import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['delay'].plot(kind='hist', bins=50, color='blue', edgecolor='black', alpha=0.7)
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['delay'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['delay'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['distance']]
    plt.boxplot(data.values, vert=False, widths=0.5, patch_artist=True, boxprops=dict(facecolor='lightblue', color='black'), whiskerprops=dict(color='black'), flierprops=dict(marker='o', markersize=5, markerfacecolor='red'), medianprops=dict(color='black'))
    plt.title('What is the average distance of flights?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Distance (miles)')
    plt.yticks([])
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['origin', 'destination']).size().reset_index(name='counts')
    data = data.sort_values(by=['counts'], ascending=False).head(10)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax.bar(data['origin'] + ' to ' + data['destination'], data['counts'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Route')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Flights')
    ax.set_title('Which airports have the highest number of flights?')
    ax.spines['top'].set_visible(False)
    ax.spines['right'].set_visible(False)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['delay', 'distance']]
    plt.scatter(data['distance'], data['delay'], alpha=0.5, color='blue')
    plt.axhline(y=data['delay'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Median Delay')
    plt.xlabel('Distance (miles)')
    plt.ylabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between distance and delay?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(loc='upper left')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['day_of_week'] = data['date'].dt.day_name()
    day_counts = data['day_of_week'].value_counts()
    day_counts.plot(kind='bar', color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Day of the Week')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Flights')
    plt.title('What is the busiest day of the week for flights?')
    plt.axhline(y=day_counts.max(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Busiest Day: {:.2f}'.format(day_counts.max()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=0)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
